        The -MENT suffix converts verbs into nouns with elegant consistency — and in Scrabble, it converts your rack into bingo territory. This 4-letter ending carries a built-in 6-point base value (thanks to the M tile worth 3), making it one of the highest-scoring suffixes before you even count the root word. With hundreds of valid MENT words in the dictionary, this suffix is a reliable pathway to 50-point bingo bonuses and game-winning plays.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring Words Ending in MENT</h2>

      <p>These -MENT words pack the heaviest scores by combining premium root letters with the already-valuable suffix. The M tile's 3-point value gives every MENT word a head start over TION equivalents.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
