      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The M Tile Advantage</h2>

      <p>What sets -MENT apart from other 4-letter suffixes is the M tile. Worth 3 points (compared to 1 for most suffix letters), it gives every MENT word a scoring edge before you even consider the root.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 MENT vs Other Suffixes</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">MENT scores <span class="text-white font-medium">6 base points</span> (M=3, E=1, N=1, T=1) compared to TION's 4 points (T=1, I=1, O=1, N=1) and NESS's 4 points (N=1, E=1, S=1, S=1). When the M lands on a Double Letter Score, that advantage doubles — giving you 9 points from the suffix alone.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Quick-Play MENT Words</h2>

      <p>These 7-letter MENT words fit naturally on most boards and score well even in tight positions. Several are bingo-eligible at exactly 7 letters.</p>

