      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bingo Strategy with MENT</h2>

      <p>The -MENT suffix pairs with short verb roots for clean 7-letter bingos. The key is recognizing which 3-letter combinations complete the word.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">3-tile root bingos:</span> PAY+MENT, GAR+MENT, SEG+MENT, TOR+MENT, MO+MENT — these require just 3 root letters alongside your MENT holding. The simpler the root, the more likely you'll draw it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">4-tile root extensions:</span> MOVE+MENT, SHIP+MENT, PLACE+MENT — these give you 8-9 letter words that span the board. Longer plays reach more premium squares and score higher base points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Double-M plays:</span> Words like COMMENT use two M tiles (worth 6 points just from the Ms). If you draw both Ms, look for MENT words that incorporate the second M into the root.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">S-hook potential:</span> Most MENT words accept an S hook (PAYMENTS, GARMENTS, SHIPMENTS). After playing your MENT bingo, the opponent must deal with the S-hook vulnerability you've created.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Positioning</h2>

      <p>The M tile's 3-point value makes premium square placement especially rewarding for MENT words. Prioritize getting M onto multipliers.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ M on Triple Letter</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M on TLS = 9 points from one tile. PAYMENT with M on TLS scores 20 base points. Position your word so the suffix's M lands on the multiplier.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ 8-Letter TWS Reach</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MOVEMENT (8 letters) with its double-M scores 15 base × 3 = 45 + 50 bingo bonus = 95 points when spanning a Triple Word Score.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Rack Management for MENT</h2>

      <p>The M tile is less common than T, I, O, or N (only 2 copies in the bag), so drawing into MENT requires patience and awareness of tile distribution.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2 copies</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M tiles in bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1-2 turns</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Max MENT hold time</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>With only 2 M tiles in the entire bag, you won't draw MENT as often as TION or NESS. When you do hold M, E, N, T together, act decisively — this combination is too valuable to waste on incremental plays. If your remaining 3 tiles include any common verb root, play the bingo immediately.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Summary</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Summary</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The -MENT suffix delivers <span class="text-white font-medium">the highest base point value of any common 4-letter suffix</span> (6 points). With the M tile worth 3 points and only 3 root tiles needed for a bingo, MENT words consistently score 60-100+ points per play. The suffix converts verbs to nouns reliably, the words accept S-hooks for follow-up plays, and the M tile multiplies beautifully on premium squares. Act fast when you draw into MENT — the 2 M tiles in the bag make this opportunity rare and precious.</p>
